race.comment: CHAMIERRO (10) has strung three wins together on the bounce and is racing with a lot of confidence of late. The draw doesn't look as bad as it first did following scratchings and he looks a very progressive type. Can easily continue the picket fence here. PERFECT PLAY (12) has won two from three over this mile journey and brings NSW formlines to the table. Looks well placed third-up where he should be reaching his peak and can bring up back-to-back wins. The consistent OCEAN ZAR (15) has remarkably hit the top-five at her past 13 starts including a well-deserved Eagle Farm win at the latest effort. Cannot be discounted lightly. EXPRESS PAYMENT (4) was too tough last start and the rise to the mile now looks ideal. Good third-up record and is expected to be in the finish.
